						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kīlaka (1428 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Records in Sanskrit written in Grantha characters that <hi rend="bold">Śrīpati,</hi> chief minister and son of <hi rend="bold">Aṇṇapa</hi> who was also a minister, made a opening (<hi rend="italic">dvāra</hi>) in the <hi rend="italic">vaḷabhī</hi> of the <hi rend="italic">Śrīraṅga-vimāna</hi> in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Kīlaka, Vaiśākha, Paurṇamī, Thursday</hi> (<hi rend="italic">vāsava-mantri-vāra</hi>) which seems to correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1428, April 29, Thursday.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
